As eNCA's Ronald Masinda reports, Ubuntu Boxing Fraternity could be the good samaritan SA boxing has been yearning for. #Dstv403 JOHANNESBURG - Many ex-boxers live broke and die penniless in South Africa. Simphiwe Vetyeka, for example, could never box again after suffering two broken legs following a car accident. But there seems to be a solution on the horizon for the likes of Vetyeka and many others from the Eastern Cape. Ubuntu Boxing Fraternity could be the good samaritan South African boxing has been yearning for.